        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-79d73447-73a0-483a-bf21-12026d95d25b">
                Mr. Benson
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-79d73447-73a0-483a-bf21-12026d95d25b" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1949-06-23/debates/0005e765-474d-4309-ae76-99a2b46d6f30/Clause16%E2%80%94(IncreaseInInitialAllowancesEtcInRespectOfMachineryOrPlant)#contribution-79d73447-73a0-483a-bf21-12026d95d25b">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">Every Act we pass is discriminatory between the people affected by it and the people who are not affected by it. In new legislation it is completely impossible to make retrospective every Amendment which gives a concession for future activities. If it is discriminatory, why stop at two years? Why not go back over the last 15?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
